## § 3 — Access Methods

List all supported access methods. Mark the primary/default method first.
Use only values from the `access_method` enum (ADR046 §2.4 + v1.1.0 Amendment):

| Method value | Definition |
|---|---|
| `mcp` | Direct MCP server invocation |
| `mcp_wrapper_around_api` | MCP server wrapping an underlying API |
| `manual_hybrid` | User-operated browser + paste-back |
| `api` | Direct API SDK invocation |
| `cli_via_bash` | Shell invocation via Bash tool |
| `subscription_chat` | Browser/desktop subscription session |
| `mobile_dispatch` | Mobile app via team_98 dispatch |
| `sdk` | Cursor SDK direct API call (v1.1.0) |
| `cursor_ide_routed` | Cursor IDE manual hybrid, subscription pool (v1.1.0) |
| `cursor_ide_cloud` | Cursor Cloud Agents, async sandboxed, within Max plan (v1.1.0) |
| `cursor_ide_bg` | Cursor Background Agents, IDE background, within Max plan (v1.1.0) |

```yaml
access_methods:
  - <primary_method>
  - <secondary_method_if_any>
default_method: <primary_method>
```

**If a NEW access_method value is needed** (not in the table above):
Describe the new method and file an ADR046 amendment request via team_100.

