## § 7 — Underlying Models (IR#1 Enforcement)

**Required for IR#1 vendor-distinctness check.** List all underlying models.
The EngineAdapter will compare `vendor` + `model_family` to enforce builder ≠ validator.

```yaml
underlying_models:
  - name: <model_name>          # e.g., gpt-4o, claude-sonnet-4-6, gemini-2.5-pro
    vendor: <vendor>             # anthropic | openai | google | cursor | perplexity | other
    model_family: <family>       # e.g., claude-sonnet, gpt, gemini, cursor-composer
  # add additional models if this engine can use multiple
```

**IR#1 implication note** (can this engine serve as IR#1 validator for anthropic-built artifacts?):

```
<Free text — e.g., "vendor=openai; valid IR#1 validator for anthropic-builder artifacts">
```

